not_countable_complex:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `exprℂ -/
/-- The complex numbers are not countable. -/
theorem not_countable_complex : ¬(Set.univ : set (exprℂ)).countable :=
  by
  rw [← le_aleph_0_iff_set_countable, not_le, mk_univ_complex]
  apply cantor
#align not_countable_complex not_countable_complex
mk_univ_complex:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.mk -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `exprℂ -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.continuum -/
/-- The cardinality of the complex numbers, as a set. -/
@[simp]
theorem mk_univ_complex : cardinal.mk (Set.univ : set (exprℂ)) = cardinal.continuum := by rw [mk_univ, mk_complex]
#align mk_univ_complex mk_univ_complex
mk_complex:

/-- The cardinality of the complex numbers, as a type. -/
@[simp]
theorem mk_complex : cardinal.mk (exprℂ) = cardinal.continuum := by
  rw [mk_congr complex.equiv_real_prod, mk_prod, lift_id, mk_real, continuum_mul_self]
#align mk_complex mk_complex
